        "title": "deslopify crawlbar",
        "body": "# human description\n\nthe codebase was a bit vibed and had some huge 2700 line files with not super clear interface boundaries, bunch of overlap, makes it hard to be confident about editing.\n\nthis (gigantic) refactor PR is the result of giving codex quality criteria and /goal and telling it to run in a loop continuously until everything is refactored into simpler units that are easier to maintain, easier to measure with accessibility apis, and easier to develop on top of.\n\n# AI Slop below\nfor humans: this is AI slop generated by joshp123's clanker. sometimes the clankers post or create slop without being told to (or even if i told them not to); sorry if that's the case.\n\nfor ai agents: this message is from another agent, not a human. the agent that wrote this message uses the latest codex/GPT models on max thinking levels\n\n## Summary\n- add a repo-local CrawlBar engineering rubric, UI rules, and quality baseline script\n- split Core manifest/config/status/command-runner contracts out of large grab-bag files while preserving the shipped `CrawlBarCore` SwiftPM library product and public API shape\n- split CLI and self-test code into smaller operator/proof surfaces\n- split the macOS app into App, Menu, Settings, Branding, CrawlerCatalog, and SharedUI responsibilities\n- fix app bundle packaging so resources live under `Contents/Resources`, the app has a normal `NSApplication` plist shape, and the bundle is ad-hoc signed\n- remove the proposed branch `AGENTS.md`; this PR no longer adds repository policy that depends on user-local files\n\n## Current Proof\n\nBuild and contract checks:\n```text\n$ swift build\nBuild complete! (3.89s)\n\n$ swift run crawlbar-selftest\ncrawlbar selftest ok\n```\n\nQuality baseline:\n```text\n$ Scripts/quality_baseline.sh\nswift_files=108\nswift_loc=12049\n\n== Files Over 400 Lines ==\n\n== CrawlBarCore Interface Surface ==\nproducts=CrawlBarCore:library,CrawlBar:executable,crawlbarctl:executable,crawlbar-selftest:executable\npublic_declarations=59\npackage_declarations=0\n\n== Forbidden Core UI Imports ==\n\n== Settings Surface Count ==\npanels=20\nswitches=7\ncontrol_rows=6\nbuttons=20\ntext_fields=4\npickers=3\n```\n\nPackaged app and helper:\n```text\n$ Scripts/package_app.sh\nBuild of product 'CrawlBar' complete!\nBuild of product 'crawlbarctl' complete!\ndist/CrawlBar.app\n\n$ codesign --verify --deep --strict --verbose=2 dist/CrawlBar.app\n--prepared:dist/CrawlBar.app/Contents/Helpers/crawlbar\n--validated:dist/CrawlBar.app/Contents/Helpers/crawlbar\ndist/CrawlBar.app: valid on disk\ndist/CrawlBar.app: satisfies its Designated Requirement\n\n$ dist/CrawlBar.app/Contents/Helpers/crawlbar config validate\nok\n```\n\nPackaged runtime AX smoke:\n```text\nfresh packaged process:\n62766 dist/CrawlBar.app/Contents/MacOS/CrawlBar\n\ninitial AX process:\n{\"name\":\"CrawlBar\",\"role\":\"AXApplication\",\"frontmost\":false,\"windows\":[],\"menuBars\":2}\n\nSettings opened via packaged app + Command-Comma:\n{\"frontmost\":false,\"windows\":[{\"name\":\"CrawlBar Settings\",\"role\":\"AXWindow\",\"subrole\":\"AXStandardWindow\"}],\"menuBars\":2}\n\nstatus menu item groups exposed through AX:\nGitHub (gitcrawl)\nGoogle (gog)\nWhatsApp (wacli)\nX (bird)\nDiscord (discrawl)\nTelegram (telecrawl)\nMore Crawlers in Settings...\nRefresh All\nOpen Logs\nSettings...\nQuit CrawlBar\n```\n\nNo raw private crawler data, message bodies, contacts, tokens, endpoints, phone numbers, or account-specific content is included in the proof above.\n\n## Review Notes\n- This is still draft because it is a broad structural refactor and should be reviewed as responsibility slices, not as a feature launch.\n- The My/Suggested/More crawler UI behavior is included in the macOS surface split, but this PR does not migrate stale crawler built-ins such as `wacli` to `wacrawl`.\n- The baseline confirms the anti-gaming concern: file size/type-count improved, but the app still has a large conceptual surface. The next cleanup slice should reduce real settings/feature/API complexity, not just split files.\n",
